The paper discusses the trade-off between achievable throughput and reliability in cooperative transmission, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need to consider different cooperation strategies depending on the multi-media content, which suggests a connection to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for careful cooperation partner selection and power allocation, which relates to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the need to fully exploit the benefits of cooperative transmission, which suggests a connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
